.ds n) explain_access_or_die
.cp 0  \" Solaris defaults to ''.cp 1'', sheesh.
.TH explain_access_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_access_or_die \- check permissions for a file and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_access_or_die(3)" \
    "check permissions for a file and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/libexplain.h>
.br
void explain_access_or_die(const char *pathname, int mode);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The explain_access_or_die function is used to call the \f[I]access\fP(2)
system call and check the result.  On failure it prints an
explanation of the error, obtained from \f[I]explain_access\fP(3), and
then terminates by calling \f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.RS
.ft CW
explain_access_or_die(pathname, mode);
.ft R
.RE
.TP 8n
\f[I]pathname\fP
The pathname, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]access\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]mode\fP
The mode, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]access\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
Returns:
Only ever return on success.
On failure process will exit.
